The paper is about automatic program repair tools, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of Java programming language suggests that it could also belong to the programming languages (cs.PL) category. The large-scale experiment and evaluation of different tools make it relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) category. The investigation of causes of non-patch generation could also make it relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category. Finally, the use of statistical analysis and machine learning techniques could make it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
